1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:10,000
Bull vs Bear Arena turns AI market analysis into blind judgment practice.

2
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:22,000
The product reverses the usual AI workflow: decide first, reveal judge scores later.

3
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:37,000
Ticker lookup validates symbols with yfinance and shows a 30-day price line.

4
00:00:37,000 --> 00:00:55,000
Bull and Bear each produce three evidence-backed opening claims.

5
00:00:55,000 --> 00:01:13,000
Round two adds targeted rebuttals with source URLs, not just opinions.

6
00:01:13,000 --> 00:01:31,000
Users submit a blind verdict before evidence, source, and logic scores are revealed.

7
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:49,000
Every verdict is saved and later backtested against real market prices.

8
00:01:49,000 --> 00:02:04,000
Demo Mode lets judges test the full workflow even when API quota is unavailable.

9
00:02:04,000 --> 00:02:22,000
Codex and GPT-5.6 shaped the full stack, schemas, prompts, tests, and UX decisions.

10
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:32,000
The goal is not trading automation. The goal is better recorded judgment.
